Login into AWS console
Choose the EC2 instances from the services
Click on launch instances to create a instances
Then choose Microsoft Windows Server 2012 R2 base  select that
Leave as it is and click  configure
No need to change anything then click on add storage 
Then  click add tags
Then configure settings
leave as it is click review and launch
Then click on launch instances
Create the new key pair(name the key pair as per your convenience) and click download key pair.
Then click on launch instances
Instance is launched successfully
You need to wait for some time to start running the instances state it takes some time, wait till 2/2 checks passed under status check.
Instance state turned into running, Note the availability zone for the currently running instance.
Choose volume in the left menu
Create volume - choose the availability zone correctly for the instance running, click create volume
After creating, right-click created volume and click attach volume, inside this add currently running instances in an instance, then click attach a volume
Go to instances and  click on current instances and give connect in the top menu
Here choose the RDP client, download the remote desktop file
Then click get password
Browse your key pair from the downloaded file and upload it
Then click on decrypt password
Then copy-paste your password into notepad
Then you open the download file from download(remote desktop file)
Then click connect
Enter the password from notepad then click ok
Click yes
Wait for a few minutes to start the remote application it will take some time
The remote desktop  server is successfully created and opened
Then terminate the remote server 
Terminate the current instance


